body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

The following is a simplified version of the test case from #1990.

```
module test #(
        parameter BUG = 1
) (
        (* nowrshmsk = !BUG *)
        output reg [1:0] x
);
        wire z = 0;
        integer i;
        always @*
                for (i = 0; i < 2; i=i+1)
                        x[z^i] = z^i;
endmodule
```

Run with `yosys -p 'prep; show' test.v`.

## Expected behavior

This should simply reduce to `x = 2'b10`. (It does with `BUG = 0`.)

## Actual behavior

Current Yosys master (8ec3b6d) produces a circuit with a topological loop.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/619764/81387840-a9f67c80-9117-11ea-9d77-bb34e881d78b.png)

(Running `opt -full` will optimize the loop away, but in the current flows there will be a warning about the loop in the intermediate circuit before it is being optimized away.)

